system:
The Twelve Caesars is a biographical work by the Roman historian Suetonius, written in the early 2nd century AD. The work consists of twelve books, each dedicated to a different Roman emperor from Julius Caesar to Domitian.

Suetonius wrote The Twelve Caesars to highlight the differences between the lives of the emperors. He wanted to show how each emperor's reign was unique, and how they shaped the Roman Empire in different ways. He also wanted to illustrate the many strengths and weaknesses of each emperor, as well as their personal quirks and flaws.

Suetonius wrote his work in a clear and concise style, with a focus on presenting the facts in a straightforward manner. He included detailed descriptions of each emperor's appearance, behavior, and accomplishments, as well as their flaws and failures. He also included anecdotes and stories from the lives of the emperors that helped to humanize them and make them more relatable to his readers.

Overall, The Twelve Caesars is a fascinating glimpse into the lives of some of the most powerful figures in Roman history, and it continues to be an important source of information about the Roman Empire for historians today.

Walt Disney was born in 1901 in Chicago, Illinois, and was the fourth of five children. He was interested in drawing and animation from an early age and was inspired by the works of L. Frank Baum and the Silly Symphonies cartoons that he watched as a child.

Disney moved to Los Angeles in 1923 to pursue a career in animation and founded the Disney Brothers Studio with his brother Roy. The studio produced the first Mickey Mouse cartoon, "Steamboat Willie," in 1928, which was a huge success and helped to establish Disney as a major player in the animation industry.

Disney continued to produce animated films throughout the 1930s, including classics like "Snow White and the Seven Dwarfs" (1937), "Pinocchio" (1940), and "Fantasia" (1940). He also launched a series of live-action films, including "Mary Poppins" (1964) and "The Jungle Book" (1967).

In 1955, Disney opened his first theme park, Disneyland, which became a major tourist attraction and helped to popularize the concept of theme parks worldwide. He went on to create Walt Disney World in Florida (1971) and Tokyo Disneyland (1983).

Disney also had a significant impact on the entertainment industry through his involvement in television and music. He produced several successful TV shows, including "The Mickey Mouse Club" (1955-1959), and launched the music label Walt Disney Records.

In addition to his work in entertainment, Disney was also involved in various philanthropic efforts throughout his life. He established the Walt Disney Foundation in 1955 to support charitable causes such as children's health and education. He also founded the California Institute of the Arts (CalArts) in 1962 to provide scholarships for aspiring artists and animators.

Disney died in 1966 at the age of 65, but his legacy continues to live on through his films, theme parks, music, and philanthropic efforts. He is widely regarded as one of the most influential figures in American popular culture and entertainment history.

En segundo lugar, prepara los filetes rebozados. En un bol, mezcla el pan rallado, harina, orégano, sal y pimienta. Agrega un huevo y batirlo con una cuchara hasta que se forme una masa homogénea. 
En tercer lugar, reboza los filetes en la masa para formar un rebozo grueso y seco. Si el rebozo es demasiado duro para frotarlo sobre la carne o es demasiado pegajoso para agarrar el filete delicadamente con las manos, use papel mantequilla para hacerlo más suave o seco, respectivamente. Agregue a los huevos al rebozo si es necesario para conseguir un mejor resultado. 
En cuarto lugar, desliza los filetes en aceite caliente hasta que estén dorados por ambos lados. Deja el pan caliente a temperatura ambiente o en un horno caliente durante 30 minutos antes de servir. 
En quinto lugar, sirve los filetes con ensalada preparada y acompañamiento adicional como arroz o papas fritas.

It aims to help readers become more aware of these biases and develop strategies to overcome them. Some of the key ideas discussed in the book include:

* Overconfidence bias: We tend to overestimate our abilities and make decisions based on insufficient information.
* Availability bias: We often make decisions based on what's immediately available to us, ignoring other options or information that might be more relevant.
* Recency bias: We tend to give more weight to recent events or information, even if they're not necessarily representative of the whole situation.
* Sunk cost fallacy: We tend to continue investing in something even if it's no longer worth it, due to the sunk cost we've already put into it.
* Status quo bias: We often stick with the status quo even when there might be better options available.

By understanding these biases and developing strategies to overcome them, we can make more informed and rational decisions in our personal and professional lives.

prompt: ### Human: "Hvað er munurinn á HTML og JavaScript?"### Assistant:
system:
HTML er en protokol for at skabe websidear og JavaScript er et programmeringsspråk som er utviklet til å brukes i websidear.

HTML er et tekstbasert format og brukes til å opprette websidear. Det brukes til å markere tekst, bilder, og andre elementer som skal vises i en webside. HTML benytter seg av tag-eksempler, hvor hvert tag representerer et element på en webside. Disse tagene brukes til å markere forskjellige elementer, inkludert tekst, bilder, og andre objekter. HTML brukes også til å sørge for at de markerte elementene blir presentert i en spesiell ordning og stil på en webside.

JavaScript er et programmeringsspråk som benytter seg av XML-tagger for å kreve data fra brukeren og endre oppsettet på en webside i løpet av bruken. Det kan utføre funksjoner som automatisk gjør det mulig for en bruker å kommunisere med en webside, inkludert valg av elementer, valg av antall kolonner, skift av stil, og utføring av logiske utfall. JavaScript benytter seg av et domene som representerer den nøyaktige posisjonen i et dokument på en webside. 

HTML og JavaScript benyttes sammen for å skape dynamiske websidear som kan endres når de kjøres. JavaScript er ofte benyttet for å utføre kompleksere operasjoner og implementere interaktivitet i en webside, mens HTML er den mest vanlige metoden for å markere elementer og struktur i en webside.
source: "Hvað er munurinn á HTML og JavaScript?"

2. Show respect: Make eye contact, nod, and use open body language to show that you are listening. This will help the speaker feel more comfortable and encourage them to continue speaking.

3. Ask questions: If you don't understand something, ask for clarification or more information. This will show that you are engaged in the conversation and want to fully understand what the speaker is saying.

4. Summarize: After the speaker has finished, summarize what they have said in your own words. This will help ensure that you have understood the speaker's point of view and will also give them a chance to correct any misunderstandings.

We hope that this paper will contribute to further research on few-shot semantic segmentation by providing more data and more powerful tools for modeling human understanding. Búðu til stutta og þægilega samantekt á greininni út frá samantekt hennar.

Few-shot learning (FSL) er ein af lykilframtíðarstigum í tölvulærdómi og vekur mikla athygli. Í þessari grein er fókusinn á FSL vandamálinu við skilning á samræðum, sem inniheldur tvo náið tengda verkefni: ásetningu á tilgangi og fyllingu á reitum. Það hefur verið sannað að samræðuskilningur hagnist mikið á að læra samhliða báðum undirverkefnunum. Hins vegar er slík samhliða lærdómur erfiður í few-shot aðstæðum: á annarri hendi aukast erfiðleikar við að módelera tenginguna milli verkefnanna vegna þess að sýnatalsþrek magnar erfiðleikana; á hinni hendi er enn frekar lítið rannsakað hvernig á að læra samhliða mörgum verkefnum í few-shot umhverfinu. Í svari við þetta kynnum við FewJoint, fyrsta FSL mælikvarða fyrir samhliða samræðuskilning. FewJoint býður upp á nýtt safn með 59 mismunandi samræðusviðum úr raunverulegum iðnaðarforritagreinum og kóðaplattform til að auðvelda uppsetningu FSL tilrauna, sem er vonast til að muni stuðla að rannsóknum á þessu sviði. Þar að auki finnum við að ófullkominn framkomur í few-shot umhverfinu leiðir oft til hávaða deilingar milli undirverkefnanna og truflar samhliða lærdóm. Til að takast á við þetta, leiðbeinum við reitum með skýrum tilgangsupplýsingum og leggjum fram nýja trúargæsluhátt sem hindrar lágt-traust tilgangsupplýsingar til að tryggja gæði deilingarinnar. Að auki kynnum við Reptile-háttar meta-lærdómsaðferð til að ná betri almennun í óséðum few-shot sviðum. 2 (5 oz) dósir Bumble Bee® Solid White Albacore Tuna, þurrkaðar
1 avókadó
2 msk Sriracha sósa
1 msk Dijon sinnep
2-3 msk sellerí, hakkað
2 msk rauðlaukur, hakkaður
2 grænlaukar, hakkaðir
1 msk fersk koriander, hakkað
Salt og pipar, eftir smekk
2 fullar skálir með blöðrur
1 skál með matchstick gulrótum
4 (10 tommu) heilhveiti tortillur
LEIÐBEININGAR:
Í meðalstórum skál, blandaðu saman tunu og avókadó þar til það er jafnt. Bættu við hinum hráefnum fram að salti og pipar, blandaðu vel.
Til að setja saman, leggðu 1/2 skál með blöðrum á hverja tortillu, 1/4 skál með matchstick gulrótum og skiptu tunu blöndunni jafnt á milli tortillanna. Rúllaðu tortilluna þétt saman, skerið í sneiðar og njóttu!

One of the biggest advantages of ReactJS is its component-based architecture. Components are reusable blocks of code that can be used to create user interface elements such as buttons, forms, and menus. This makes it easy to create modular and maintainable code that can be updated and reused without affecting the rest of the application.
